values.comments:
This course is for those who have completed Latin 204, Latin 212, or equivalent (such as placement score of 650, or AP score of 4 or 5). Close reading and discussion of a Latin author or a particular genre of latin literature. Topics will vary each semester, and the course may be repeated for credit. For current topic visit the Classical Studies department website.&#8232;&#8232;

Students overall reflected on positive experiences from Professor Farrell’s course. Though the required texts were often challenging, students found them “enjoyable” and “fascinating,” also claiming that “It was a pleasure to read an entire book in Latin.” Students who took the class wished, however, that there could have been a bit more emphasis placed on Latin grammar.&#8232;&#8232;

Students felt privileged to have had Professor Farrell as an instructor, calling him “wonderful” and “excellent.” Students especially favored his extensive knowledge about the classics, praising his ability to “bring in so much to any class that he teaches.”&#8232;&#8232;

Despite generally favoring the course content and the instructor, students had a hard time with the methods of assessment utilized. They claimed uncertainty in knowing ahead of time how much each graded assignment was worth.
